Key Match Events: Domantas Sabonis tied the game going 2-for-2 from the free throw line with 51 seconds remaining.
Keon Ellis drew a foul with 0.2 seconds left in the first overtime and made one of two free throws to tie the game.
DeMar DeRozan scored the final 9 points for the Kings in the second overtime, finishing with a team-high 30 points.
Malik Monk had a clear look at the basket but was blocked by Haywood Highsmith in the first overtime.
Jaime Jaquez Jr missed both free throws with 4.1 seconds left in the first overtime, allowing the Kings to tie the game.
Post-Match Reflections: Doug Christie rode the players who led the comeback and let them finish the game, showing his faith in them.
The players expressed their willingness to fight for Doug Christie and appreciated his belief in them.
The Kings extended their win streak to 5 games.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Keon Ellis had 15 deflections in the game, playing fantastic defense.
Domantas Sabonis played 50 minutes and finished with 21 points, 18 rebounds, 11 assists, 3 blocks, and 1 steal.
Keegan Murray had 14 points, 12 rebounds, and played fantastic defense, significantly limiting Tyler Herro's impact in the fourth quarter and overtimes.
Malik Monk, despite his inefficiency, added timely buckets late in the game and contributed 6 assists, 5 rebounds, and 2 steals.
